The diaries, 1917-1977, are relatively complete, but Morgenstern did not write daily or
            every month. There are significant gaps: 1918-1920; Feb.-May 1938; March 1946-Jan. 1947;
            and Sept. 1951-Feb. 1952. Shorter gaps also occur in April-May 1924, Sept. 1925;
            June-July 1948; and April 1949. The diaries are in the Writings and
               Speeches Series.
